#summary Tutorials: Creating a new persistent object without transactions.
#labels Phase-Support

{{{
                SimplePersistent persistentObject = new SimplePersistent("1");
                persistentObject.setValue("Hello World");
                
                repository.create(persistentObject);
}}}

 # Create the object and set its values. 
 # Add it to the repository using the create method.
 # The parameters of the create method are:
  * the new instance of the persistent object.
  * the return value is the instance of the newly created persistent object. Use this value for further persistence operations.

Create method ensures an object with the same identity doesn't exist in the repository, otherwise a !KeyViolationException is thrown.

{{{
                assertFalse(repository.contains("1"));
                repository.create(new SimplePersistent("1"));
                // Will throw KeyViolationException
                repository.create(new SimplePersistent("1"));
}}}

